

The $LCIO/rootio directory contains files related to the test of using ROOT I/O for LCIO.


  ROOTDict.mk:  example make file for creating an LCIO dictionary (A.Naumann)

  readevent.C:  example macro for reading in an example tree w/ LCIO data  
	

additional files added for ROOT I/O :

 $LCIO/src/cpp/include/RIO/*.h
 $LCIO/src/cpp/src/RIO/*.cc


###############################################################

 Build instructions:
 -------------------

. /data/gaede/root/5.24.00/bin/thisroot.sh

cd
mkdir lcio 
cd lcio

export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.freehep.org:/cvs/lcio
cvs co -d rio_v00-00 -r rio_v00-00 lcio


cd rio_v00-00
mkdir build 

cd build 
cmake -D BUILD_ROOTIO=ON -D ROOT_HOME=$ROOTSYS ..
make -j 4 install



#------- run the example :

./bin/rootio ../rootio/DST01-06_ppr004_bbcsdu.slcio dst.root

root -l
# root [0] .x ../rootio/lciotree.C

###############################################################


